wned Survivor will cancel Blood Fury, but conserve any remaining Charges. Cool-down time: 3 seconds. Blood Fury will end if The Oni is stunned with a Pallet if the Power gauge is either above 99 Charges or below 5 Charges. This allows the Game to play the Blood-Fury-to-Idle animation. Demon Dash: Charge time: 2 seconds Cool-down time: 1 second Movement speed: 7.82 m/s or 195.5 % Demon Dash Yaw scale (horizontal): 44 % Demon Strike: Charge time: 2 seconds Charge threshold: 0.35 seconds Holding the Attack button for longer than this will initiate a Demon Strike instead of Quick Attack and vice versa. It should be noted that a Quick Attack while in Blood Fury is considered a Special Attack and will not apply effects such as the double-damage of the Exposed Status Effect, for example. Attack open time: 0.5 seconds Attack hitting time: 0.3 seconds Attack cool-downs: Successful hit: 3 seconds Missed/Obstacle hit: 2 seconds Attack Yaw scale (horizontal): 27.5 % Cool-down Yaw scale (horizontal): 12 % (6.6 % with Gamepad) Cool-down Pitch scale (vertical): 25 % (13.75 % with Gamepad) Maximum Attack Yaw speed (horizontal): uncapped This refers to the maximum speed at which The Oni can turn during a Demon Strike. Maximum Attack Turn angle: 540 ° This is the maximum angle The Oni can turn to the left or right during a Demon Strike. Power Gauge: Capacity: 100 Charges Passive gain: +0.2 Charges per second. This gain is capped at 98 Charges, requiring the absorption of at least one Blood Orb to fill the Power gauge. Active gain: Absorbing Blood Orbs: +2.5 Charges Successful Basic Attack: +40 Charges This only applies to healthy Survivors being put into the Injured State.Downing Survivors does not grant this bonus.",
